1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:31,000
OPPORTUNITY COST. Every choice has a hidden trade-off.

2
00:00:31,000 --> 00:01:02,000
CHOOSE A = GIVE UP B. The best alternative you give up is the opportunity cost.

3
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:32,000
MOMO CAN ONLY CHOOSE ONE. Fish now, or playtime first?

4
00:01:32,000 --> 00:02:02,000
WHAT MOMO GIVES UP. Choosing the fish means giving up playtime.

5
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:32,000
COMFORT VS GROWTH. A nap has value. Learning has value too.

6
00:02:32,000 --> 00:03:03,000
YOUR DAILY CHOICES. Time, money, attention, and energy all have trade-offs.

7
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:34,000
MOMO’S 3-STEP METHOD. Choose clearly. Compare the best alternative. Think long-term.

8
00:03:34,000 --> 00:04:05,000
PAUSE BEFORE YOU CHOOSE. A three-second pause can change the decision.

9
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:35,000
BETTER ORDER, BETTER OUTCOME. Sometimes the best choice is changing the sequence.

10
00:04:35,000 --> 00:05:05,400
NEXT: SUPPLY & DEMAND. Subscribe for Episode 2.
